18/10/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov announced on Tuesday (October 17th) that Bulgaria will participate in projects of the NATO Consultation, Command and Control Agency (NC3A).
Agency chief Dag Wilhelmsen is spending four days in the country, studying prospects for Bulgarian companies in NC3A programmes.
One of them, the Field Integrated Communications and Information System, could be used by Bulgarian troops participating in military missions abroad.
In other news Tuesday, Interior Minister Rumen Petkov announced that Europol would open a bureau in Sofia at the end of this month.
Petkov was meeting with German counterpart Wolfgang Schaeuble in Berlin.
(Darik, Bulgarian Government website, BNR - 17/10/06)
